"{\"uid\": \"firstalert4.com-2024-05-24-manchester-officers-put-work-fundraise-special-olympics\", \"text\": \"MANCHESTER, Mo. (First Alert 4) - Local law enforcement took time out Thursday to help the Missouri Special Olympics.  Manchester officers took off the badge and put on an apron. These officers were bussing tables tonight at Tucker's in Manchester.  A portion of tonight's sales will go to Special Olympics Missouri. This fundraiser is something these local officers have made a tradition.  They have been doing this fundraiser since 2007 and have raised more than $180,000 so far.  Copyright 2024 KMOV. All rights reserved.\"}"